  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2025-01-09",
    "date": "2025-02-03T16:22:40Z",
    "text": "This joint resolution proposes a constitutional amendment limiting the pardon power of the President.\n\nThe amendment prohibits the President from granting a pardon or reprieve to himself or herself, to relatives or members of the administration, to paid campaign employees, to a person or entity for an offense motivated by an interest of any of those people, or to a person or entity for an offense directed by or coordinated with the President.\n\nThe amendment also invalidates pardons issued for a corrupt purpose."
  },
